<subSubSection id="A64F625E52AFF20CA6FDCF1E52D98DC0" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="0D1A2033DAA65F59B90842B47D868E99" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F5E1AC08216D48CF4C70847E0D7D1067" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">
<bibRefCitation id="506DE622312F64E4B46D10AAC9D0DC77" author="Verity, R" journalOrPublisher="Entomologist's Record" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" refId="B98" refString="Verity, R, 1920. Seasonal Polymorphism and Races of Some European Grypocera and Rhopalocera. Additional Notes. Entomologist's Record 32: 3-8, 140-152." title="Seasonal Polymorphism and Races of Some European Grypocera and Rhopalocera. Additional Notes. Entomologist's Record 32: 3 - 8, 140 - 152." year="1920">Verity (1920)</bibRefCitation>
proposed this name as a 
<normalizedToken id="45CD5C92C47D5D834E1A234982ABC337" originalValue="“race”">&quot;race&quot;</normalizedToken>
of 
<taxonomicName id="A4F29038AA0E9B01B9C488C70934A167" genus="H." lsidName="H. alveus" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" rank="species" species="alveus">
<emphasis id="0138CBAB4084F3DD0D2A42CD9ABD78A9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">H. alveus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="FBF3C37AE30812EB253D4A9A669792A6" originalValue="Hübner">Huebner</normalizedToken>
, [1803]. As it was given in trinomy and the content of the description clearly indicates that a geographical race was meant, this name is available as subspecific (article 45.6 
<bibRefCitation id="A1ABA45CC6536C31079C47724DAB6464" author="ICZN" journalOrPublisher="Internationale Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" publicationUrl="http://www.iczn.org/iczn/index.jsp" refId="B47" refString="ICZN, 1999. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth edition. London. [available online at http://www.iczn.org/iczn/index.jsp" title="International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth edition. London. [available online at" url="http://www.iczn.org/iczn/index.jsp" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
). The year on the specimen labels (1937) indicate specimens were collected 17 years after description (1920) from the same location the original holotype material was collected. As a result, the black label of the specimens treated as 
<normalizedToken id="5559A3E6675EE80049E71E53F8E55C6D" originalValue="“types”">&quot;types&quot;</normalizedToken>
is erroneous. The specimen collected from the same geographical location from which the type specimen was collected is called topotype. According to ICZN (1999), a topotype has no formal standing and is not regulated by the Code. Therefore, these four specimens are erroneously labelled as types, should be annotated as &quot;Not a Type&quot; and are treated here as 
<normalizedToken id="E417B009CBBADCC6A92B2032149315DD" originalValue="“Non-type”">&quot;Non-type&quot;</normalizedToken>
specimens
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
